POE-Component-IRC-Plugin-CoinFlip

This module is a L<POE::Component::IRC> plugin which uses
L<POE::Component::IRC::Plugin> for its base. It provides interface to
"flip" coins (heads or tails) on IRC.
It accepts input from public channel events, C</notice> messages as well
as C</msg> (private messages); although that can be configured at will.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc POE::Component::IRC::Plugin::CoinFlip

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=POE-Component-IRC-Plugin-CoinFlip

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/POE-Component-IRC-Plugin-CoinFlip

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/POE-Component-IRC-Plugin-CoinFlip

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/POE-Component-IRC-Plugin-CoinFlip


